sec.p:
Following the NCI recommendations [41], GI50, TGI and LC50 parameters were calculated for each extract:
The GI50 value is the concentration where 100 × (T − T0)/(C − T0) equals 50 and measures the growth inhibitory power of the examined extracts;
The TGI value is the concentration of the tested extract where 100 × (T − T0)/(C − T0) equals 0 and measures the cytostatic effect;
The LC50 value is the concentration of the drug where 100 × (T − T0)/T0 equals 50 and measures the cytotoxic effect of extracts.
